These are Puzzles for 1x2 Level 3

.:: Puzzle 1x2-Level-3-1::.
The people use 2 different means of transport: roller, skateboard
1. the person driving the skateboard is on the far left or far right##3
2. the person driving the roller is on the right of the person driving the skateboard##1

.:: Answer ::.
|            |    1     |   2   |
| Transport   | skateboard | roller |

 #################################

 
.:: Puzzle 1x2-Level-3-2::.
There are 2 different favourite beverages: tea, hot-chocolate
1. the person drinking tea is on the left or right of the person drinking hot-chocolate##3
2. the person drinking hot-chocolate is on the right of the person drinking tea##1

.:: Answer ::.
|       |     1     |      2      |
| Beverage   | tea | hot-chocolate |

 #################################

 
.:: Puzzle 1x2-Level-3-3::.
The people grow 2 different varities of flowers: dahlia, balloon-flower
1. the person who growsballoon-flower is on the left or right of the person who growsdahlia##3
2. the person who growsballoon-flower is on the left of the person who growsdahlia##1

.:: Answer ::.
|         |      1      |    2    |
| Flower   | balloon-flower | dahlia |

 #################################

 
.:: Puzzle 1x2-Level-3-4::.
2 different brands of cigars are smoked: fonseca, prince
1. the prince-smoker is on the left of the fonseca-smoker##1
2. the fonseca-smoker is on the left or right of the prince-smoker##3

.:: Answer ::.
|               |  1   |   2   |
| Cigar   | prince | fonseca |

